 Geschichte, Politik und Gesellschaft. Thematisiert werden sowohl unterschiedliche fachdisziplinäre Zugänge als auch sprachliche Phänomene (wie Lexeme, Textsorten, rhetorische Figuren) sowie politische, historische und soziale Strukturen (u.a. Akteure, Medien, Erinnerung). Exemplarische Analysen machen zudem deutlich, dass Geschichte, Politik und Gesellschaft voneinander untrennbare Teilbereiche gesellschaftlicher Wissenskonstitution sind.   aThis work examines the linguistic construction of knowledge in history, politics, and society. It presents a range of disciplinary approaches, linguistic phenomena (such as lexemes, text types, and rhetorical tropes), and political, historical and, social structures (such as actors, media, and commemoration). Case analyses reveal that history, politics, and society are inextricably interlinked in the social construction of knowledge.   aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Aug 2020) 0aCommunication in politics. 0aDiscourse analysisxPolitical aspects. 0aSociolinguistics. 4aGesellschaftliche Kommunikation. 4aGroup Communication. 4aLanguage in Politics. 4aPolitical Communication. 4aPolitische Kommunikation. 4aPolitische Sprache. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aRoth, Kersten Sven, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWengeler, Martin, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aZiem, Alexander, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus eBook-Package 2017z978311071954308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2017z9783110540550oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Social Sciences 2017z9783110548242oZDB-23-DSW0 cEPUBz97831103950750 cprintz978311029586340uhtt